issues.why:
The shared fixture writer inverts the documented layout — it appends the trailing comma to the *last* element and omits it from all the others, the exact opposite of the prompt's "every element line ending in a trailing comma except the last". The gold survives because it strips a trailing comma unconditionally, but almost every test therefore pins an input shape the prompt never describes; only the two hand-written literal fixtures (`"[

{"id": 1},


{"id": 2},
{"id": 3}

]
"`) exercise the real format, so a solution that keyed comma-stripping to the documented position would be judged wrongly.

